criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All consecutive cirrhotic patients who have undergone TIPS at our Department for
             bleeding of esophagogastric varices refractory to medical or endoscopic treatment or
             for ascites/hydrothorax refractory to diuretic therapy will be considered eligible for
             the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  an age >75 years; past or present history of hepatic encephalopathy;

          -  a Z-score at trial making test-A (TMT-A) >1.5;

          -  bilirubine levels >5 mg/dl;

          -  creatinine levels >3 mg/dl;

          -  serious cardiac or pulmonary dysfunction;

          -  a Child-Pugh's score >11;

          -  a model end-stage liver disease (MELD) score >18;

          -  portal thrombosis;

          -  a diagnosis of hepatic carcinoma;

          -  sepsis;

          -  spontaneous bacterial peritonitis;

          -  renal insufficiency.
